Ndubuisi Orji, Abuja The House of Representatives has approved N346.388 billon budget for the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC) for the 2019 financial year  ending on May 31, 2020. After a clause by clause consideration of the budget by  the Committee of Supply, it was approved, yesterday, during  a plenary presided over the speaker,  Femi Gbajabiamila. A breakdown of the budget indicates that  N22.338 billion   is for personnel cost, N13.466billion  for  overhead expenditure,  while  N4.083 billon   is for Internal Capital Expenditure. Also, the sum of  N306.500 billion was approprited  for developmental projects in the Niger Delta. Speaking with journalists, after the approval of the budget, Chairman, House Committee on NDDC, Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo, said the parliament will ensure that the budget is well utilized.. He expressed  the hope that with the passage of the budget, things would  begin to take shape in the oil producing states. According to him, “NDDC, has witnessed many setbacks, the  region is suffering despite billions of naira budgeted for its development, now that the Commission has a budget to work with, the narration is going to change for good, it is no longer going to be business as usual” .